experiment_description: Different beginning reward checkpoints - In this experiment, the smallest reward checkpoints are increased and decreased, such that the length of the pure exploration part of the FrAngel algorithm could be increased or decreased and eventually provide different quality fragments that can be explored after that.

iterations.final_grammar:
1: Program = begin
    state = Init
    Blocks
    End
end
2: Init = mc_init(start_pos)
3: Blocks = Block
4: Blocks = begin
    Block
    Blocks
end
5: Block = while true
    Move
    Bool || break
end
6: Block = Move
7: Block = if Bool
    Move
end
8: Move = mc_move!(state, Direction, Times, Sprint, Jump)
9: Direction = ["forward"]
10: Direction = ["back"]
11: Direction = ["left"]
12: Direction = ["right"]
13: Direction = ["forward", "left"]
14: Direction = ["forward", "right"]
15: Direction = ["back", "left"]
16: Direction = ["back", "right"]
17: Bool = mc_was_good_move(state)
18: Bool = mc_has_moved(state)
19: Bool = mc_is_done(state)
20: Bool = !Bool
21: End = mc_end(state)
22: Times = 1
23: Times = 2
24: Times = 3
25: Times = 4
26: Sprint = true
27: Sprint = false
28: Jump = true
29: Jump = false
